  "_comment_purpose": "Explorer log matrix override for the CI test runs. Applied by the runner-validation-windows workflow (copied to %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Decentraland\\MetaForge\\log-matrix.json before mf explorer test). REPLACES the build's source-side matrix (ReportsHandlingSettingsProduction/Development) for the duration of the run.",
  "_comment_semantics": "isOverride=true → this matrix is the sole source of truth for the CI run, independent of whatever the build's source-side matrix has enabled. severity is the MINIMUM level enabled per category (Log<Warning<Error<Exception<Assert). Categories NOT listed here are FULLY silenced (no Exception, no Assert). When adding a new category to unity-explorer DCL.Diagnostics.ReportCategory, add it here too — at Log by default — otherwise it will be invisible in the CI runs.",
  "_comment_tiers": "Default is Log (full verbosity) for every category — this preserves Error/Exception/Assert visibility on top of the diagnostic Log+Warning stream. Spammers observed in prior runs are demoted: Warning skips the Log firehose; Error would also skip Warnings (not used today — no spammer was caught producing noisy Warnings in run 25917112690).",
